about.summary: Creates dummy columns from columns that have categorical variables (character or factor types). You can also specify which columns to make dummies out of, or which columns to ignore. Also creates dummy rows from character, factor, and Date columns. This package provides a significant speed increase from creating dummy variables through model.matrix().

name: r-fastdummies
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.6.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-fastdummies
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/fastDummies_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/fastDummies/fastDummies_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 323340e9be7b2dbdcedb4eb6c30a38e9f4164a2a3a1639e31d6e87906760753a

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-data.table
    - r-tibble
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-data.table
    - r-tibble

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('fastDummies')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('fastDummies')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/jacobkap/fastDummies
  license: MIT
  summary: Creates dummy columns from columns that have categorical variables (character or factor
    types). You can also specify which columns to make dummies out of, or which columns
    to ignore. Also creates dummy rows from character, factor, and Date columns. This
    package provides a significant speed increase from creating dummy variables through
    model.matrix().
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - uday1889
